WEBVTT

00:02.770 --> 00:05.073
[ Slow Asian music plays ]

00:11.445 --> 00:13.414
Who is this, again?

00:13.447 --> 00:15.516
It's your mom's
great-aunt's second cousin,

00:15.549 --> 00:17.451
so very closely related.

00:17.485 --> 00:18.719
Are those
her sisters?

00:18.752 --> 00:20.488
Yes.
They were triplets.

00:20.521 --> 00:23.291
Trina was the oldest,
then Gina, then Yu-Mei.

00:24.758 --> 00:27.361
If I were a triplet,
I'd have one do my homework,

00:27.395 --> 00:30.598
one do my chores,
and one get into shenanigans.

00:30.631 --> 00:32.133
They're not your clones.

00:32.166 --> 00:33.934
Also, you're one of them.

00:33.967 --> 00:36.337
Oh, n you're into math.

00:37.638 --> 00:41.075
Oh, no. I got a stain
on the tie I borrowed from Dad.

00:41.109 --> 00:43.211
My year of bad luck
just won't end.

00:50.551 --> 00:53.254
Really?
That seems disrespectful.

01:00.828 --> 01:03.831
Okay.
I guess it can't hurt.

01:03.864 --> 01:06.033
[ Hawks, spits ]

01:07.735 --> 01:09.803
I was supposed to spit
into the handkerchief

01:09.837 --> 01:11.672
and put that in the casket,
wasn't I?

01:18.546 --> 01:21.915
**

01:21.949 --> 01:23.217
Mom, where's Connie?

01:29.823 --> 01:30.958
How nice.

01:34.195 --> 01:35.829
[ Sighs ]

01:44.472 --> 01:45.906
We should go
grab our seats --

01:45.939 --> 01:47.708
near the back,
in case your aunt sings.

01:47.741 --> 01:48.642
Hello.

01:48.676 --> 01:49.643
Hello.
Hello.

01:49.677 --> 01:51.145
You look well.

01:51.179 --> 01:52.646
You too.
Have you eaten?

01:52.680 --> 01:54.382
Not yet, but I will.

01:54.415 --> 01:55.549
Are you warm enough?

01:55.583 --> 01:57.685
Yes. I brought
a light sweater.

01:57.718 --> 01:59.520
Good.

01:59.553 --> 02:01.922
I'm going to go find a chair
with some padding.

02:01.955 --> 02:04.625
The wood on these
looks subpar.

02:04.658 --> 02:05.626
Nice to see you.

02:05.659 --> 02:07.361
Okay.
Nice to see you.

02:08.729 --> 02:09.763
Who was that man?

02:09.797 --> 02:11.299
Oh,
that was my father.

02:12.733 --> 02:15.102
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:15.135 --> 02:16.270
* Fresh off the boat

02:16.304 --> 02:17.971
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

02:18.005 --> 02:20.274
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

02:20.308 --> 02:21.542
* Fresh off the boat

02:21.575 --> 02:23.877
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

02:23.911 --> 02:25.346
* But I know where I'm goin'

02:25.379 --> 02:28.115
* I'm fresh off the boat

02:28.148 --> 02:30.218
Hold up.
That was your dad?!

02:30.251 --> 02:31.852
What?
[ Scoffs ]

02:31.885 --> 02:33.754
Oh, you thought
he would look older?

02:33.787 --> 02:36.023
What can I say?
We have good genes.

02:36.056 --> 02:38.859
We didn't know you had a dad.
You never talk about him.

02:38.892 --> 02:40.093
I thought he was dead.

02:40.127 --> 02:42.596
Of course he's not dead.

02:42.630 --> 02:45.399
No one in my family has died
before the age of 90 --

02:45.433 --> 02:48.836
except for Great-Uncle Xi,
and he loved his menthols.

02:48.869 --> 02:50.504
He used to swallow
the butts.

02:50.538 --> 02:52.840
So, how come we've never met
our grandfather?

02:52.873 --> 02:54.675
You've met him.

02:54.708 --> 02:56.977
He waved at you
through the hospital window

02:57.010 --> 02:58.279
after you were born.

02:59.280 --> 03:01.148
He's a diplomat,
and he works all over the world,

03:01.181 --> 03:02.683
so we didn't see him
that much.

03:02.716 --> 03:05.386
So, when did he get divorced
from Grandma Chu?

03:05.419 --> 03:07.821
Divorced?!
Don't be ridiculous!

03:07.855 --> 03:09.423
They're still married.

03:09.457 --> 03:11.559
And they still see each other
every few years,

03:11.592 --> 03:13.394
and he always sends her coasters
from the Hard Rock

03:13.427 --> 03:14.995
in every city he visits.

03:15.028 --> 03:16.297
I've seen those.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.299
That means your dad's
been to Copenhagen.

03:18.332 --> 03:20.067
He travels a lot.

03:20.100 --> 03:22.202
That's how it always was
in my family.

03:22.236 --> 03:24.272
My mom was around,
My dad was away.

03:24.305 --> 03:26.139
I didn't see my dad much,
either --

03:26.173 --> 03:27.808
because
he was always working.

03:27.841 --> 03:30.311
He worked literally
up until the day he died --

03:30.344 --> 03:31.612
like George Burns.

03:31.645 --> 03:33.146
Godfather of comedy.

03:33.180 --> 03:35.483
We miss you, George --
every day.

03:35.516 --> 03:36.784
* Yeah

03:38.352 --> 03:40.988
So many questions.
What's so hard to understand?

03:41.021 --> 03:42.356
We grew up
in a different time.

03:42.390 --> 03:44.492
We had a different relationship
with our parents.

03:44.525 --> 03:46.093
Our boys are luckier
than we were.

03:46.126 --> 03:47.495
I feel lucky enough.

03:47.528 --> 03:49.497
Well, you have to admit,
it would've been nice

03:49.530 --> 03:51.231
if your dad had made it
to our wedding.

03:51.265 --> 03:54.001
We had our reception
in a car dealership.

03:54.034 --> 03:56.169
Honestly, Louis, I haven't
given it a second thought.

03:56.203 --> 03:58.439
[ Woman laughing loudly ]

03:58.472 --> 04:01.775
Of course, Cousin Karen
is wearing a strapless dress.

04:01.809 --> 04:03.577
It's, like,
"We get it, Karen.

04:03.611 --> 04:06.046
You have the best shoulders
in the family."

04:06.079 --> 04:09.350
**

04:09.383 --> 04:11.852
[ Sighs ] Shoot.
I can't find Dad's tie.

04:11.885 --> 04:14.054
First I stain it,
then I lose it?

04:14.087 --> 04:16.457
Relax. There's, like,
never a time in my life

04:16.490 --> 04:17.991
when something
isn't lost.

04:18.025 --> 04:19.560
Well, I'm not you.

04:20.894 --> 04:22.796
Sorry. I'm jet-lagged.

04:22.830 --> 04:24.465
It was the layover
in Atlanta.

04:24.498 --> 04:25.633
Big hub.

04:25.666 --> 04:28.135
I'm sorry. I can't help you
look for the tie.

04:28.168 --> 04:29.837
I'm revising
my will and trust.

04:29.870 --> 04:31.772
I was talking to Aunt Lynn
at the funeral

04:31.805 --> 04:33.774
and realized
I haven't updated it

04:33.807 --> 04:35.709
since we first moved
to Orlando.

04:35.743 --> 04:37.010
Few things.

04:37.044 --> 04:38.346
Who's Aunt Lynn?

04:38.379 --> 04:41.081
Also, since when do you have
a will and trust?

04:41.114 --> 04:43.384
I don't know.
How old are you in preschool?

04:43.417 --> 04:44.918
Good thing
I looked at it.

04:44.952 --> 04:47.120
I forgot I named Honey
as my executor.

04:47.154 --> 04:49.122
I need to change that.

04:49.156 --> 04:51.759
She's shown herself
to be too emotional
in the face of tragedy.

04:51.792 --> 04:53.827
Reporter: Diana's public life

04:53.861 --> 04:55.796
began and ended the same way --
[ Sobbing ]

04:55.829 --> 04:58.131
with the paparazzi in pursuit.

04:58.165 --> 04:59.900
Whoa.

04:59.933 --> 05:01.802
Yeah, she maxed out
all our credit cards

05:01.835 --> 05:04.338
buying Princess Di
commemorative plates.

05:04.372 --> 05:05.806
I ate a piece of pizza
off one of them.

05:05.839 --> 05:07.441
She didn't speak to me
for two days.

05:07.475 --> 05:09.843
Why?!

05:09.877 --> 05:11.679
I need the executor
of my will

05:11.712 --> 05:14.382
to be composed and responsible
when the time comes.

05:14.415 --> 05:17.250
I don't care about anything
after I die. I'm dead.

05:17.284 --> 05:20.588
Of course you don't --
because you're so selfish.

05:20.621 --> 05:21.889
I'm sorry.

05:21.922 --> 05:24.257
I'm still worked up
about the layover in Atlanta.

05:24.291 --> 05:27.595
How can you have three Cinnabons
and all of them are closed?

05:27.628 --> 05:30.097
**

05:30.130 --> 05:32.332
You know I don't like change,
Madame Xing.

05:32.366 --> 05:33.901
I'm happy
with what I know.

05:33.934 --> 05:35.703
It's what I was used to
growing up.

05:35.736 --> 05:37.371
But then,
when I was in Texas,

05:37.405 --> 05:40.307
I started thinking --
maybe there's another way.

05:40.340 --> 05:42.810
But is it
too late to try?

05:42.843 --> 05:44.745
Did I miss my chance?

05:44.778 --> 05:45.879
[ Sighs ] No.

05:45.913 --> 05:48.582
I can't talk to Louis
about it.

05:48.616 --> 05:50.884
He'd just turn it
into a big deal.

05:52.085 --> 05:53.854
Mm.

05:53.887 --> 05:56.457
**

05:56.490 --> 05:58.659
It's all in the wrist.
Eh?

05:58.692 --> 06:00.193
All right,
we have our drinks.

06:00.227 --> 06:01.261
So, tell me all about

06:01.294 --> 06:03.597
this Jessica conversation
you overheard.

06:03.631 --> 06:05.766
So, she was, uh,
having her monthly call

06:05.799 --> 06:07.200
with her psychic,
Madame Xing.

06:07.234 --> 06:08.602
Uh-huh.
And she was talking

06:08.636 --> 06:10.438
about her relationship
with her father,

06:10.471 --> 06:12.740
wondering if she missed
her chance to connect with him.

06:12.773 --> 06:15.242
Now, I knew she felt this way
deep down. I mean, I get it.

06:15.275 --> 06:17.277
I had a distant relationship
with my dad, too.

06:17.310 --> 06:19.613
I don't think my dad
even knew my middle name.

06:19.647 --> 06:20.948
Zeus.

06:20.981 --> 06:22.382
Um...

06:22.416 --> 06:23.784
But Jessica's so stubborn,

06:23.817 --> 06:25.853
she would never admit
her true feelings to me,

06:25.886 --> 06:28.922
which is why it's so great that
the second triplet just died.

06:28.956 --> 06:31.959
Triplets? I love triplets.
Big fan.

06:31.992 --> 06:33.894
I mean, it's not great
that she died, but she was 90.

06:33.927 --> 06:35.028
There are sadder things.

06:35.062 --> 06:36.997
Marvin! Ha!

06:37.030 --> 06:39.132
It's finally here!

06:39.166 --> 06:41.835
This is the one where Diana is
holding Bubbles the chimp

06:41.869 --> 06:43.471
with Michael Jackson.

06:43.504 --> 06:45.739
I need you
to move your medals.

06:47.407 --> 06:48.942
Anyway, you were saying?

06:48.976 --> 06:51.178
So, Jessica and I are going
to another funeral, in Houston,

06:51.211 --> 06:53.213
and her dad is
going to be there again.

06:53.246 --> 06:55.182
Now, if she won't
talk to me about it,

06:55.215 --> 06:57.117
at least I can get her
to talk to him.

06:57.150 --> 06:59.286
Houston,
we have a solution!

06:59.319 --> 07:01.522
I'm gonna bring my wife
and her dad together.

07:01.555 --> 07:03.090
[ Both chuckle ]

07:06.393 --> 07:07.895
Mmm!
This wine is great!

07:07.928 --> 07:10.163
White wine after 5:00 p.m.
is for the ladies.

07:10.197 --> 07:11.732
We men have to get it in
during the day. [ Chuckles ]

07:16.236 --> 07:19.172
[ Slow Asian music plays ]

07:21.909 --> 07:24.144
You can't boss me around
anymore, Gina.

07:24.177 --> 07:25.879
I can finally wear miniskirts.

07:28.982 --> 07:31.752
Very sad. Very sad.

07:31.785 --> 07:33.320
Ooh!
There's your dad.

07:34.555 --> 07:36.323
Mr. Chu, hello.

07:36.356 --> 07:39.026
You two want to go look
at the casket together or...?

07:39.059 --> 07:40.861
I already got in there.

07:40.894 --> 07:43.030
She looks handsome
and serene.

07:43.063 --> 07:46.867
**

07:46.900 --> 07:48.636
Uh...Jessica,

07:48.669 --> 07:50.538
why don't you sit
next to your dad?

07:50.571 --> 07:52.540
And, Mrs. Chu,
why don't we go get some tea?

07:54.107 --> 07:55.242
The tea here is great.

07:58.579 --> 08:00.981
Louis,
she doesn't want tea.

08:01.014 --> 08:02.916
We could just sit
somewhere else.

08:02.950 --> 08:06.587
**

08:06.620 --> 08:09.056
Uh, Jessica, I was
just talking to your dad

08:09.089 --> 08:10.558
about all the miles
we're racking up

08:10.591 --> 08:12.292
flying back and forth
to these funerals.

08:12.325 --> 08:13.794
Probably adds up
to a free ticket.

08:13.827 --> 08:15.395
Christmas is
just around the corner.

08:15.428 --> 08:17.931
I want to use my miles
to go to Barcelona.

08:17.965 --> 08:18.932
Oh!

08:18.966 --> 08:20.968
Do you mean
"Barthelona"?

08:21.001 --> 08:27.007
**

08:27.040 --> 08:29.276
[ Squealing ]

08:31.745 --> 08:33.947
Eddie, I have
a serious question for you.

08:33.981 --> 08:34.982
Just do it in the shower.

08:35.015 --> 08:36.817
What?
Hm?

08:36.850 --> 08:38.786
Okay.

08:38.819 --> 08:40.053
I just wanted to ask you

08:40.087 --> 08:41.755
if you would be
the executor of my will.

08:41.789 --> 08:43.691
Really?
You want me to do it?

08:43.724 --> 08:45.292
Yeah.
You're my oldest brother.

08:48.762 --> 08:50.497
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, okay.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.065
I'll do you proud,
little bro.

08:52.099 --> 08:53.400
Excellent.

08:53.433 --> 08:56.136
I just need to go
get this notarized by Deidre.

08:56.169 --> 08:58.405
She's not the best notary
I've worked with,

08:58.438 --> 08:59.940
but she did my patent,

08:59.973 --> 09:02.009
so I wanted to throw her
more business.

09:02.042 --> 09:03.543
**

09:03.577 --> 09:05.613
Uh, I was thinking --
you two never did

09:05.646 --> 09:07.615
a father/daughter dance
at our wedding.

09:07.648 --> 09:09.516
I could ask the organist
if she knows any Journey.

09:10.884 --> 09:12.285
No, thank you.No, thank you.

09:13.887 --> 09:15.222
[ Sighs ]

09:15.255 --> 09:16.924
Louis.

09:16.957 --> 09:19.126
What's going on?
Why are you being so weird?

09:19.159 --> 09:21.061
I heard you talking
to Madame Xing.

09:21.094 --> 09:22.362
You said you wish you had

09:22.395 --> 09:23.964
a closer relationship
with your dad,

09:23.997 --> 09:25.766
but you feel like
you missed your chance.

09:25.799 --> 09:27.601
Missed my chance?

09:29.336 --> 09:31.304
I was talking
about chicken!

09:31.338 --> 09:33.140
Everyone in Houston
was trying to push

09:33.173 --> 09:35.475
the barbecue chicken on me,
and I said no,

09:35.508 --> 09:38.378
but then I worried that I missed
out on something amazing.

09:38.411 --> 09:40.480
Oh, come on. You said
you couldn't talk to me about it

09:40.513 --> 09:42.482
because you thought
I'd turn it into a big deal.

09:42.515 --> 09:43.851
You would.

09:43.884 --> 09:46.854
Every time I eat something new,
you make a big deal out of it.

09:46.887 --> 09:49.089
Remember the first time
I tried pecan pie?

09:49.122 --> 09:50.724
**

09:50.758 --> 09:52.392
Huh? Huh? Huh?

09:52.425 --> 09:53.526
Amazing, right?

09:53.560 --> 09:55.595
First it's sweet,
then comes the salt.

09:55.629 --> 09:57.731
Talk to me. Talk to me.
What are you thinking?
What are you feeling?

09:57.765 --> 10:00.533
Back...off.

10:00.567 --> 10:02.602
**

10:02.636 --> 10:04.571
So, you weren't talking
about your dad on the phone?

10:04.604 --> 10:08.041
No. I was talking Texas barbecue
chicken with my psychic.

10:08.075 --> 10:09.609
Why is that so hard
to understand?

10:10.644 --> 10:12.512
Okay, I guess --
if you insist you were

10:12.545 --> 10:14.147
talking about
barbecue chicken.

10:14.181 --> 10:16.449
Louis, my relationship
with my father is fine.

10:16.483 --> 10:17.718
Stay out of it.

10:18.686 --> 10:20.453
[ Scoffs ] Chicken?

10:20.487 --> 10:21.655
More like bull.

10:21.689 --> 10:22.656
[ Chuckles ]

10:22.690 --> 10:27.327
**

10:27.360 --> 10:28.361
[ Sniffs ]

10:28.395 --> 10:31.631
**

10:34.134 --> 10:37.470
A casserole from Amanda --
one of my HOA associates.

10:37.504 --> 10:39.006
According to this note,

10:39.039 --> 10:40.708
she thinks I have
a terminal illness.

10:41.909 --> 10:44.344
When I asked Deidre
to notarize my will,

10:44.377 --> 10:46.980
she must've told
Carol-Joan...

10:47.014 --> 10:49.349
who told Lisa...

10:49.382 --> 10:51.584
who told
that blabbermouth Amanda,

10:51.618 --> 10:53.754
and I can only imagine
who s told.

10:53.787 --> 10:55.255
[ Indistinct talking ]

10:55.288 --> 10:57.457
I think they even called me once
in the confusion.

10:57.490 --> 10:58.558
[ Women gasp ]

10:58.591 --> 11:00.761
**

11:00.794 --> 11:02.329
[ All sobbing ]

11:02.362 --> 11:04.998
And now they all think
I'm dying.

11:12.239 --> 11:14.507
Eddie told me you picked him
as your will person.

11:14.541 --> 11:16.076
Executor.
Whatever.

11:16.109 --> 11:17.444
Why wouldn't you
choose me?

11:17.477 --> 11:19.046
As soon as
your bad-luck year ends,

11:19.079 --> 11:21.749
I'll revise my will again
and make you executor.

11:21.782 --> 11:24.217
Oh. So Eddie's
just a temp?

11:24.251 --> 11:26.586
Of course.
You're the reliable one.

11:26.619 --> 11:28.055
But let's face it --

11:28.088 --> 11:29.990
right now, you can't even
keep track of a tie.

11:30.023 --> 11:32.692
Actually, I meant to tell you --
I found Dad's tie.

11:32.726 --> 11:34.627
Maybe my luck
is turning around.

11:34.661 --> 11:36.129
Maybe.

11:36.163 --> 11:39.967
**

11:40.000 --> 11:41.668
So,
she's in total denial.

11:41.701 --> 11:44.271
Mm. She doesn't think
her relationship with
her dad is a problem.

11:44.304 --> 11:45.672
Ha! They never do.

11:45.705 --> 11:48.075
And now we have to go
back to Houston for a wedding.

11:48.108 --> 11:50.677
Gina had always forbade Yu-Mei
from marrying

11:50.710 --> 11:52.345
and from picking
an American name,

11:52.379 --> 11:53.914
for reasons no one knows.
Hm.

11:53.947 --> 11:55.048
And now that Gina's passed,

11:55.082 --> 11:56.884
Yu-Mei has given herself
the name "Madison"

11:56.917 --> 11:58.886
and is finally marrying
the love of her life --

11:58.919 --> 12:00.687
Roger,
a retired greengrocer.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.355
We're going to see
Jessica's dad,

12:02.389 --> 12:04.191
but I can't force them
to connect.

12:04.224 --> 12:06.794
They'll probably just talk about
food or the weather.

12:06.827 --> 12:08.896
Even my dad and I had
more things to talk about,

12:08.929 --> 12:10.263
like competitive crabbing.

12:10.297 --> 12:12.599
Yeah, my dad loved
to talk about flags.

12:12.632 --> 12:15.235
I just don't want Jessica to
have any regrets down the road.

12:15.268 --> 12:16.904
Her dad's not getting
any younger.

12:16.937 --> 12:18.438
I'm missing two!

12:18.471 --> 12:20.874
Oh. Uh, well, Honey,
we -- we were just --

12:20.908 --> 12:23.443
I-I'm missing Diana Coronation
and Diana at Centre Court.

12:23.476 --> 12:24.444
I--

12:24.477 --> 12:28.348
[ Dramatic music plays ]

12:28.381 --> 12:30.017
Lift up your pizza.

12:30.050 --> 12:31.418
Party's over, Lou.

12:31.451 --> 12:37.090
**

12:37.124 --> 12:39.092
Cheeseburger tater tot
casserole?

12:39.126 --> 12:40.828
Respect, Lisa.

12:43.596 --> 12:44.564
[ Chuckles ]

12:44.597 --> 12:45.565
Don't do that.

12:45.598 --> 12:46.967
Sorry. Can't help it.

12:47.000 --> 12:49.502
Just practicing my big-bro
ruffle, like big brothers do.

12:49.536 --> 12:50.637
You're technically older,

12:50.670 --> 12:52.072
but I'm the one
everybody counts on.

12:52.105 --> 12:53.473
Not everyone.

12:53.506 --> 12:55.375
Evan chose me to be
his will person.

12:55.408 --> 12:57.377
He trusts me with his stuff,
not you.

12:58.511 --> 12:59.746
[ Sighs ]
I said don't do that.

12:59.779 --> 13:01.882
You're getting tot grease
in my bangs.

13:01.915 --> 13:03.917
You sound mad,
middle brother.

13:05.352 --> 13:06.419
Evan didn't pick you.

13:06.453 --> 13:08.088
He's just waiting out
my year of bad luck,

13:08.121 --> 13:09.756
and then he's gonna make me
his will person --

13:09.789 --> 13:10.757
because I'm better.

13:10.790 --> 13:12.725
You're just
a temporary fix.

13:12.759 --> 13:14.828
**

13:14.862 --> 13:16.563
[ Sighs ]

13:18.832 --> 13:20.633
I deserve
these empty calories.

13:20.667 --> 13:22.870
Hope they go
straight to my thighs.

13:25.973 --> 13:27.540
Jessica,
we're going to be late!

13:27.574 --> 13:29.642
Jessica: I don't rush you when
you're blow-drying your hair!

13:29.676 --> 13:33.013
Don't rush me when I'm
lint-rolling my travel cardigan!

13:34.147 --> 13:35.482
What's with
all the casseroles?

13:35.515 --> 13:37.150
The neighborhood ladies
think I'm dying.

13:37.184 --> 13:38.451
It's a long story.

13:38.485 --> 13:39.953
Well, I don't have time
to hear it.

13:39.987 --> 13:41.121
I should feel guilty,

13:41.154 --> 13:43.223
but I'm enjoying
all the love I'm getting.

13:43.256 --> 13:45.658
There's a two-page note here
from Carol-Joan.

13:45.692 --> 13:46.994
Carol-Joan?

13:47.027 --> 13:49.162
I thought you two hadn't spoken
since the hedge feud.

13:49.196 --> 13:51.331
You know how people change
when they think you're dying.

13:51.364 --> 13:53.901
It's time to focus
on what matters.

13:54.935 --> 13:56.069
Right.

13:56.103 --> 13:58.305
Death brings people
together.

13:58.338 --> 14:04.411
**

14:04.444 --> 14:05.913
Your dad is dying.

14:09.883 --> 14:10.783
My dad is dying?

14:10.817 --> 14:12.685
How do you know?
He told me.

14:12.719 --> 14:14.121
He asked me not to tell you.
He's very private.

14:14.154 --> 14:15.388
But the important thing is,

14:15.422 --> 14:17.457
now's your chance
to really connect with him --

14:17.490 --> 14:19.126
make the best of the time
you have left.

14:19.159 --> 14:20.493
I should go talk to him.

14:20.527 --> 14:22.829
Yes, but, uh...maybe don't
bring up the "dying" thing.

14:22.862 --> 14:23.997
He's a proud man.

14:24.031 --> 14:25.498
[ Scoffs ]

14:25.532 --> 14:26.967
He's dancing now.

14:27.000 --> 14:28.601
[ Dance music plays ]

14:28.635 --> 14:30.103
I'll wait.

14:31.071 --> 14:33.440
Good.
Good for him.

14:33.473 --> 14:35.342
**

14:35.375 --> 14:36.476
[ Knock on door ]

14:36.509 --> 14:38.478
Grandma, can I talk to you
for a sec?

14:42.916 --> 14:43.984
[ Sighs ]

14:44.017 --> 14:45.152
Okay.

14:46.886 --> 14:49.022
Do you really think spitting
straight into the casket

14:49.056 --> 14:50.357
and not
into your handkerchief

14:50.390 --> 14:51.925
could have made
my bad luck worse?

14:54.161 --> 14:57.264
I got mad about something that
normally wouldn't bother me,

14:57.297 --> 14:59.199
and Eddie and I
got into a fight.

14:59.232 --> 15:01.601
I feel like I'm changing
into a different person.

15:01.634 --> 15:02.569
Hm.

15:02.602 --> 15:04.037
Eddie was just being
so annoying --

15:04.071 --> 15:06.706
pretending to care about Evan,
when he really doesn't.

15:14.614 --> 15:16.383
Yeah,
Eddie owes everyone money.

15:22.622 --> 15:24.091
Wait -- Dad's tie?

15:25.158 --> 15:26.793
So I didn't find it.

15:26.826 --> 15:28.861
Eddie replaced it for me?

15:40.607 --> 15:41.874
[ Dance music plays ]

15:41.908 --> 15:42.875
[ Music stops ]

15:42.909 --> 15:44.077
[ Applause ]

15:44.111 --> 15:45.278
[ Sighs ]

15:45.312 --> 15:46.846
Thirsty.

15:51.251 --> 15:53.820
Hi, Dad.
How you feeling?

15:53.853 --> 15:54.988
Are you tired?

15:55.022 --> 15:56.756
A little.

15:56.789 --> 15:58.725
Would you like to sit?

15:58.758 --> 16:00.560
Not yet.

16:00.593 --> 16:01.928
A-Are you going to sit?

16:01.961 --> 16:03.763
Eventually.

16:06.566 --> 16:08.368
[ Hushed ] Come on!
You think he's dying!

16:08.401 --> 16:10.037
Weather turned hot.

16:10.070 --> 16:11.638
Oh, it has.

16:11.671 --> 16:12.939
[ Clicks tongue ]

16:12.972 --> 16:14.907
Can you breathe okay?

16:14.941 --> 16:15.942
I'm fine.

16:15.975 --> 16:17.844
I-It's not that hot.

16:17.877 --> 16:19.212
[ Chuckles softly ]

16:22.415 --> 16:23.483
Well, see you later.

16:23.516 --> 16:25.018
Okay, see you later.

16:26.953 --> 16:28.088
Really?!

16:28.121 --> 16:29.556
That's it?!

16:29.589 --> 16:32.159
You think your dad's dying,
and that's all you have to say?

16:32.192 --> 16:34.327
Don't you want to thank him
for all he's done?

16:34.361 --> 16:36.563
Don't you want to know
what he thinks about you?

16:36.596 --> 16:37.697
Invite him to Christmas?

16:37.730 --> 16:39.366
Make sure he sees you
play guitar?

16:39.399 --> 16:41.434
I don't play guitar.
You do.

16:41.468 --> 16:42.769
What if
he really was dying?

16:42.802 --> 16:43.970
Wouldn't you want him
to know

16:44.003 --> 16:45.805
that you met your dream girl
in college

16:45.838 --> 16:48.075
or that crabbing
shouldn't be a competition

16:48.108 --> 16:49.409
or that you love improv?

16:49.442 --> 16:51.478
Or that you're sorry
the last time he saw you

16:51.511 --> 16:53.413
was when you ran
out of a hot tub naked?

16:53.446 --> 16:57.117
No goodbye -- just my bare ass
running out of the water!

16:57.150 --> 16:59.252
I missed my chance
to get to know him,

16:59.286 --> 17:01.254
and I regret it every day!

17:01.288 --> 17:04.657
[ Pachelbel's
"Canon in 'D' Major" plays ]

17:05.858 --> 17:08.128
Oh, not today!

17:08.161 --> 17:11.331
I've been planning this
for 70 years!

17:11.364 --> 17:13.500
Go, Joanne! Go!

17:13.533 --> 17:18.338
**

17:20.307 --> 17:21.374
What are you doing?

17:21.408 --> 17:22.875
I'm just thinking about
that robot housekeeper

17:22.909 --> 17:23.910
from "The Jetsons".

17:23.943 --> 17:25.945
Do you think
Rosie wanted to be there?

17:25.978 --> 17:28.615
Grandma told me about the tie.
Thank you.

17:28.648 --> 17:29.916
Oh, it's no big deal.

17:29.949 --> 17:31.651
You were just so stressed
about losing it,

17:31.684 --> 17:33.086
and I was at the mall
anyway,

17:33.120 --> 17:35.822
trying to help Trent
find flattering overalls.

17:35.855 --> 17:37.290
It took a while.

17:38.491 --> 17:41.261
I'm sorry
I was a jerk earlier.

17:41.294 --> 17:42.595
I was a jerk, too.

17:42.629 --> 17:44.597
When Evan asked me to be
his will person,

17:44.631 --> 17:46.133
I didn't know
I was just a placeholder.

17:46.166 --> 17:47.300
It was just cool

17:47.334 --> 17:49.202
thinking I could be
the big brother for once.

17:49.236 --> 17:51.204
You're a great
big brother.

17:51.238 --> 17:53.306
You replaced that tie
without even telling me.

17:53.340 --> 17:54.507
When you're having
a bad year,

17:54.541 --> 17:57.444
sometimes, you just need
good stuff to happen.

17:57.477 --> 17:58.645
Trust me -- I know.

17:58.678 --> 18:00.613
This bad-luck year sucks.

18:00.647 --> 18:02.449
Want to know a secret?

18:02.482 --> 18:04.617
This "year of the bad luck"
thing?

18:04.651 --> 18:06.186
It's just puberty.

18:06.219 --> 18:09.122
And it gets worse and lasts
way longer than a year.

18:09.156 --> 18:10.157
Oh, no.

18:10.190 --> 18:11.891
At least
we're in it together.

18:12.925 --> 18:14.727
Emery, quick question
for my will.

18:14.761 --> 18:16.396
Who do you want
to get my half

18:16.429 --> 18:19.166
of the Huang Boys'
Detective Agency?

18:19.199 --> 18:22.769
[ Mid-tempo rock music plays ]

18:22.802 --> 18:25.104
Congratulations!
Thank you so much.

18:27.006 --> 18:29.276
Did you really think
I was dying?

18:29.309 --> 18:30.610
For a minute.

18:30.643 --> 18:33.613
No one in our family
has died before 90.

18:33.646 --> 18:35.215
Except Great-Uncle Xi,

18:35.248 --> 18:38.185
and that was his own fault --
for smoking and doing parkour.

18:38.218 --> 18:39.419
He never knew his limits.

18:39.452 --> 18:40.820
[ Scoffs ]

18:40.853 --> 18:42.389
[ Music continues ]

18:47.594 --> 18:51.198
Would you like to come to our
house for Christmas this year?

18:51.231 --> 18:52.165
Oh.

18:52.199 --> 18:53.366
Uh...

18:53.400 --> 18:54.734
if you'd like.

18:54.767 --> 18:57.237
There's a nice Hard Rock
in Orlando.

18:57.270 --> 18:59.272
I do like Hard Rocks.

18:59.306 --> 19:01.541
We could take a picture
in front of the big guitar!

19:01.574 --> 19:04.311
I just got a new camera!
[ Chuckling ] Oh!

19:04.344 --> 19:05.912
[ Sighs ]

19:05.945 --> 19:07.680
Are you as uncomfortable
as I am?

19:07.714 --> 19:10.583
Never been more uncomfortable
in my whole life.

19:10.617 --> 19:11.584
[ Chuckles ]

19:11.618 --> 19:12.952
Nobody wants this.

19:12.985 --> 19:14.221
We really don't.

19:14.254 --> 19:15.855
[ Sighs ]

19:15.888 --> 19:18.591
Well, nice to see you.

19:18.625 --> 19:20.893
I'll continue to keep tabs
on you through your mother.

19:20.927 --> 19:22.962
Great.
I'll do the same.

19:27.200 --> 19:28.901
Jessica.

19:28.935 --> 19:32.071
When the time does come,
just know --

19:32.104 --> 19:33.906
all my affairs
are in order.

19:33.940 --> 19:36.476
It won't be
a hassle for you.

19:36.509 --> 19:37.444
Thank you.

19:37.477 --> 19:41.080
**

19:44.651 --> 19:46.819
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:46.853 --> 19:48.555
It's before 5:00.
It's fine.

19:48.588 --> 19:50.890
I can't believe
you did that, Louis.

19:50.923 --> 19:53.826
You know how many times
I wanted to tell you
your mother's dying?

19:53.860 --> 19:56.263
I know.
I feel terrible.

19:56.296 --> 19:58.965
It's possible I'm working
through stuff with my own dad.

19:58.998 --> 20:00.500
Yes.

20:00.533 --> 20:01.834
I don't get it.

20:01.868 --> 20:04.437
How can you be okay
not being close to your dad?

20:04.471 --> 20:06.673
I just learned to appreciate
our relationship

20:06.706 --> 20:08.107
for what it is.

20:08.140 --> 20:09.909
I guess I never got there.

20:09.942 --> 20:11.043
[ Inhales deeply ]

20:11.077 --> 20:12.979
I still have
a lot of regrets.

20:13.012 --> 20:14.814
Well, you don't
have to feel alone.

20:14.847 --> 20:16.983
You always have someone
you can talk to.

20:17.016 --> 20:18.451
[ Chuckles ]

20:19.952 --> 20:21.120
I don't know, Madame Xing.

20:21.153 --> 20:22.922
I just feel like
if he'd gotten the chance

20:22.955 --> 20:25.892
to see me do improv,
it would have brought us closer.

20:27.594 --> 20:29.296
Sure, yeah,
I'm familiar with Dana Carvey.

20:29.329 --> 20:31.030
He's a genius.
[ Chuckles ]

20:33.065 --> 20:34.166
[ Doorbell rings ]

20:36.068 --> 20:37.036
[ Gasps ]

20:37.069 --> 20:38.805
Evan!
You're still upright!

20:40.172 --> 20:41.874
You guys love your tuna.

20:41.908 --> 20:43.042
I'm not dying, Lisa.

20:43.075 --> 20:44.511
Please tell everyone --
no more casseroles.

20:44.544 --> 20:45.545
Thank youuuuuuu!

20:45.578 --> 20:46.713
It's a miracle!

20:50.850 --> 20:51.684
Reporter:
In Monte Carlo this week,

20:51.718 --> 20:52.919
Princess Grace of Monaco --

20:52.952 --> 20:53.953
this quarter of a century
and more --

20:53.986 --> 20:55.221
died tragically...

20:56.155 --> 20:58.325
Hey, hey.
English only.

20:58.358 --> 21:00.192
It's what Princess Grace
would have wanted.

21:00.226 --> 21:01.628
I love the name "Grace".

21:01.661 --> 21:03.463
It would be
a good English name for me.

21:03.496 --> 21:05.432
You're never getting
an English name.

21:05.465 --> 21:06.699
Or wearing miniskirts.

21:06.733 --> 21:09.135
Ooh!
There's Nancy Reagan.

21:09.168 --> 21:10.603
And Princess Diana.

21:10.637 --> 21:13.806
One day, when you're gone,
I'm gonna change my name

21:13.840 --> 21:15.274
and have
a beautiful wedding.

21:15.308 --> 21:17.777
And it's gonna be inspired
by Princess Grace's funeral

21:17.810 --> 21:21.514
because it is beautiful
and tragic, like my life.

21:22.549 --> 21:25.552
Ooh!
Roger Moore!

